comments: Payton (NYK) makes brief contact with Mahinmi (WAS) during the screen but does not restrict his FOM.
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes himself in Payton's (NYK) path during the pick and does not deliver contact.
Beal (WAS) slightly extends his left forearm into Payton (NYK) during his drive but does not dislodge him from his legal guarding position.
Brown Jr. (WAS) makes marginal contact with Dotson (NYK) after the release of his shot attempt at the basket.
Mahinmi (WAS) firms up in a screening position in Payton's (NYK) path and does not deliver the contact.
Dotson (NYK) places his forearm to Matthews's (WAS) chest but does not extend it and dislodge him from his defensive position.
Brown Jr. (WAS) makes contact with Randle (NYK) but does not dislodge him from his rebounding position.
Beal (WAS) makes marginal contact with Payton (NYK) off ball.
Randle (NYK) and Beal (WAS) make incidental contact with each other off ball.
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Payton (NYK) and does not deliver contact.
Payton (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Beal's (WAS) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Payton's (NYK) left foot is out of bounds on the baseline when he makes contact with the ball.
Mahinmi (WAS) makes contact to Payton's (NYK) arm and body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) makes arm to head contact with Randle (NYK) during his shot attempt at the rim.
Payton (NYK) grabs Mahinmi's (WAS) hand following the pick and restricts his FOM.
Mahinmi (WAS) establishes himself in Payton's (NYK) path during the pick and does not deliver contact.

Randle's (NYK) knee makes contact with the ball and dislodges it from Beal's (WAS) possession as Beal attempts to release the pass.  Randle then makes incidental contact to Beal's arm and body after the ball is out of his possession.
Randle (NYK) maintains his legal guarding position as he defends Brown Jr. and does not affect his SQBR.
Brown Jr. (WAS) briefly grasps Robinson's (NYK) jersey during the inbounds pass.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Mahinmi (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position and makes clean contact with the ball at the end of Randle's (NYK) drive.
Randle (NYK) initiates marginal contact to Mahinmi during his drive that does not dislodge him from his defensive position.
Mahinmi (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball and causes Randle (NYK) to bobble the ball in mid-air.  He then regains control of the ball in the air and legally lands before releasing the pass.
Robinson (NYK) and Brown Jr. (WAS) engage and disengage during the rebound.

Payton (WAS) reaches in and makes contact with the ball while Robinson (NYK) is in possession.  Robinson maintains possession and Brown Jr. (WAS) reaches in and makes contact to his arm that affects his shot attempt at the rim.
Randle (NYK) commits a take foul on Brown Jr. (WAS).
Portis (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Payton II (WAS) and does not deliver contact.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal hand to arm contact with Mahinmi (WAS) during the rebound.
Portis (NYK) commits a take foul on Brown Jr. (WAS).
